Implemented the upstream-style conversation cache flow in [nemotron_audio_in.py](/home/khkramer/src/aiewf-eval/src/multi_turn_eval/services/nemotron_audio_in.py) and updated [test_nemotron_audio_in_service.py](/home/khkramer/src/aiewf-eval/tests/test_nemotron_audio_in_service.py).

State machine summary: the service now owns `_canonical_messages`; each turn appends only the latest user message to that canonical prefix. Tool-call turns commit the assistant tool-call message, then store predicted tool results in `_pending_tool_result_messages`. On the next user turn, those pending tool results are baked into full canonical context and, when suffix cache is active, sent as the suffix before the latest user message. After a successful request, old pending results are cleared and replaced only if the current turn produced new tool calls. The old tool-call disable guard is removed.

