Main concern: tool-result content is still a prediction: `{"status": "success"}`. That matches the current catchall behavior, but if real handlers start returning varied content, the canonical cache bookkeeping will need a way to capture the actual result. The canonical-history approach also assumes the same service instance observes the conversation from the start.

